    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presented in concours-level condition, this 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The powerplant exhibits exceptional compression across all rotor faces, benefiting from a comprehensive vacuum system refresh using high-temp silicone lines to ensure boost-pattern linearity. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, delivering power to the rear wheels with surgical precision. The aluminum double-wishbone suspension remains tight, preserving the chassis's celebrated 50/50 weight distribution and high-speed lateral stability. The exterior retains its factory depth and luster, while the interior is free of the typical UV-related plastics degradation or bolster wear. This is a mechanically transparent, turn-key investment for the discerning collector.",
